Two likely causes:

**1. `BindingContext` is never set.** You need to assign your ViewModel to the page:

```csharp
// In code-behind (e.g., MainPage.xaml.cs)
public MainPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
}
```

**2. ViewModel doesn't notify the UI of changes.** Implement `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or use the `[ObservableProperty]` source generator from the MVVM Community Toolkit):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;

public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title = "Hello";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description = "World";
}
```

The most common culprit is #1 — without `BindingContext`, the `{Binding}` expressions have nothing to resolve against.
